"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-03-simone-biles-defends-husband-wears-olympic-gold-medal-21355580\", \"text\": \"Simone Biles has hit out at 'f**ing miserable' critics who slammed her husband for wearing one of her Olympic gold medals inParis.  The American superstar has had another incredibly successful games in the gymnastics arena, winning three gold medals to bring her overall tally at theOlympicsto a remarkable seven.  She's won the team, all-round and vault events, and could yet win more gold in the beam and floor finals on Monday.  Follow\\u00a0Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the Paris 2024 Olympics  Throughout the games she's been supported in the crowd by her husband Jonathan Owens, himself anNFLstar with theChicagoBears.  The 29-year-old was in fact given time off from the Bears' pre-season training camp in order to go to Paris.  However, some on social media took exception to a photo on his Instagram account of the pair with Owens wearing one of Biles' medals.  'That's Simone's gold medal you are holding, not yours my guy,' one comment read, while another said: 'Why he holding it like he won it.'  Biles has now directly responded to the critics, replying to one on a TikTok comment, saying: 'Crazy thing is, I put my medal on every single one of my family members and took pictures.  'So do not ever make assumptions. Like you all are so f***ing miserable. Leave us alone.'  There were of course plenty of fans who defended the couple and lauded Owens' support of his wife.  As well as fend off internet trolls, Biles alsoreignited her feud with former USA teammate MyKayla Skinnerin Paris.  For more stories like this,check our sport page.  Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.  ArrowMORE:Shelly-Ann Fraser-Pryce out of Olympics 100m final after injury and late rule change  ArrowMORE:Fans clash at Olympics as man rips Taiwan banner out of woman's hands  ArrowMORE:Imane Khelif says 'I am a woman' after winning Olympic boxing medal  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\"}"